Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @carrot{1}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into 2cm pieces. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into wedges. Pop both onto a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over the @cumin seeds{1/2%tsp}, some @salt{}, @pepper{} and a little @olive oil{}. Toss well to evenly coat the veggies in the oil then pop onto the top shelf of the oven and roast until the veggies are tender and slightly coloured, ~{25-30%minutes}.

In the meantime, roughly chop the @dill{1} and @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest, then cut the @lemon{1} into wedges. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Pop the herbs, lentils and lemon zest into a #mixing bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Lay a @British chicken breasts{2} on a #chopping board{} and cover with a piece of #clingfilm{}. Use a #rolling pin{} or the base of a #saucepan{} to bash it until 1cm thick all over. Repeat for the other breasts. Pop the @dukkah mix{1} in a #small bowl{} and mix with a small splash of @olive oil{1%tsp per person}. Spread the dukkah over the top of each chicken breast.

> Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

When the veggies have 10-12 minutes left, give the tray a shake and move the veggies to one side of the tray. Pop the chicken breast fillets onto the other side and return to the top shelf of the oven. Cook until the chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken is cooking, put the @spiced honey mustard{1} into another small bowl. Squeeze in the juice from two lemon wedges and add the @olive oil{1}(for the dressing), to make the dressing. Whisk together with a #fork{} and add a small splash of @water{} to loosen the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the veggies and chicken are cooked remove the tray from the oven and mix the roasted carrot and onion in with the lentils, along with any cooking juices left on the tray. Pour over the dressing and add the @wild rocket{40} to the bowl. Gently fold all the ingredients together then share onto plates. Thickly slice the chicken then pop on top of the lentils and serve with any spare lemon wedges. Enjoy!